  "statement": "# Counting Bits\n\nReturn an array where index `i` contains the number of set bits in `i` for every `0 <= i <= n`.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Example 1**\n\n```text\nInput: n = 2\nOutput: [0,1,1]\n```\n\n**Example 2**\n\n```text\nInput: n = 5\nOutput: [0,1,1,2,1,2]\n```\n\n**Example 3**\n\n```text\nInput: n = 0\nOutput: [0]\n```\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Inputs are sized for local offline execution.\n- Return the value described by the method signature.",
  "editorial": "Use direct arithmetic, matrix indexing, or bit operations to preserve the required invariants while keeping extra state small.",
  "solution_notes": "```python\nclass Solution:\n    def countBits(self, n):\n        out = [0] * (n + 1)\n        for i in range(1, n + 1): out[i] = out[i >> 1] + (i & 1)\n        return out\n```",
  "hints": [
    "Watch fixed-width integer boundaries where the prompt requires them.",
    "For matrix mutation, mark or capture affected rows and columns before overwriting."
  ],
